      <Notes><![CDATA[  A collaborative research agreement between the Peoples' Republic of China's (PRC) Chinese Academy of Sciences and the United States Department of Energy, signed in August of 1987, has resulted in the compilation and exchange of several data sets that will be useful in reconstructing past climates in China, extending and calibrating instrumental records, and addressing potential CO2-induced global and regional warming.
<br><br>
  This report describes one of the twelve PRC proxy data sets exchanged as part of this bilateral agreement.  These records contain the total monthly number of rain days and rainy hours (by 6 hour periods) for Beijing during May, June, and July.  These records may be used to examine long-term summer and diurnal precipitation trends for Beijing.  These records may also be used to verify and calibrate proxy data sets, such as the dryness/wetness indices, from Beijing.]]></Notes>
